# Security Rules

Follow the security rules in `rules/common/security.md`.

## Critical Rules

- NEVER hardcode secrets, API keys, passwords, or tokens
- Validate ALL user inputs at system boundaries
- Sanitize file paths to prevent directory traversal
- Use parameterized queries for database access
- Error messages must NOT leak sensitive information
- Review template outputs for injection risks

## Before Committing

Run the security review: see `agents/security-reviewer.md` and `skills/security-review/SKILL.md`.

